==English==
===Adjective===
'''curve'''
#(''obsolete'') Bent without angles; crooked; curved.
#:''a curve line''
#:''a curve surface''

====Translations====
''See'' '''[[crooked]]''' ''and'' '''[[curved]]'''

=== Noun ===
'''curve'''  (''plural'' '''[[curves]]''')

#A gentle [[bend]], such as in a road.
#(''geometry'') A [[one-dimensional]] figure of [[non-zero]] length and (usually) containing no [[straight]] portions and no [[angle]]s.
#(''informal, usually in plural'' '''curves''') The attractive shape of a woman's body.

